Officials of the Edo State Public Works Volunteers (PUWOV) have apprehended a three men over illegal logging in Edo State. It was gathered that the men were caught while felling and transporting trees at a forest reserve in Imoga community of Akoko-Edo LGA. Speaking with journalists on the development, Edoâ€™s PUWOV Commander, Mukhtar Yusuf-Osagie, said the suspects were apprehended following a tip off and had been handed over to the police.